annotationA: Nuclear pore complex protein Nup88; Essential component of nuclear pore complex. Selectively required for the nuclear import of the Rel family transcription factors dorsal (dl) and Dorsal-related immunity factor (Dif) and the activation of an immune response. Required for the anchoring of Nup214 and emb on the nuclear envelope and thereby attenuates nuclear export signal (NES)-mediated nuclear export
annotationB: Nucleoporin at 44A, isoform A; Structural constituent of nuclear pore. It is involved in the biological process described with: oogenesis; regulation of mitotic cell cycle; regulation of meiotic cell cycle; Belongs to the WD repeat SEC13 family
